277
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:07,860
Like this.

278
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,220
(Ready and waiting)

279
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:10,340
Who's going first?

280
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:11,220
Me, I'll go first.

281
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:11,820
Go for it.

282
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:12,620
Off you go.

283
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:13,860
Back straight. Look sharp.

284
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:15,500
So strict.

285
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:17,020
Head of the family.

286
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:17,940
(Best big bro in Tui City)

287
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:19,140
I'm kidding.

288
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,740
Just talk more to loosen up.

289
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:21,780
I'm getting the energy going,

290
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,060
Once we start filming,

291
00:07:23,060 --> 00:07:24,140
I'll go quiet.

292
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:25,580
(Time to crack the case)
Keep each other on their toes.

293
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:26,420
No.

294
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:28,260
We're about to
find out who the killer is.

295
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:28,860
(Suddenly serious)

296
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:29,780
So who's the killer?

297
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:30,260
(Just asking like that?)

298
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:31,780
I guess

299
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:32,140
it's him.

300
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:33,660
She does this every time.

301
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:34,740
(Used to it)
Every single time.

302
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:35,860
I say it's him.

303
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:36,980
You know why?

304
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:38,220
Nobody's even died yet,

305
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:39,140
and I'm already the killer.

306
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:40,700
Haven't even killed anyone.

307
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,220
(To be fair)
You can't know until someone acts.

308
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:43,260
What do you think?

309
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:44,300
(Curious)
Am I right?

310
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:45,060
I think it's you.

311
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:47,340
You think it's me?

312
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:48,180
Ning, not again.

313
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:49,700
You're doing this to me again.

314
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,340
(Happy to tease)

315
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:52,940
Detectives are always the good guys.

316
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,100
The detectives

317
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,420
can't possibly kill anyone?

318
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,060
Impossible.

319
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:59,260
But that doesn't mean they
know everything,

320
00:07:59,260 --> 00:07:59,780
you get me?

321
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:00,580
He could also be totally...

322
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:01,860
(Clueless)

323
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:02,820
A bumbling detective.

324
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:03,420
Exactly.

325
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:04,940
He can't kill,

326
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:06,020
but what he says

327
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:06,900
isn't necessarily true.

328
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:07,620
(Spoken from experience)
Got it.

329
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,740
So who's the detective today?

330
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:10,940
Me.

331
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,620
You're the detective?

332
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:15,020
Alright, my turn to act.

333
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:16,540
I've got a ton of lines

334
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:18,140
Go get 'em, old pro.

335
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:19,820
(Watching Ning head off)

336
00:08:19,820 --> 00:08:21,100
When we do our scene,

337
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,180
everyone has to watch?

338
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:22,860
(Strike a pose first)
Right.

339
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:24,060
I probably won't be able to see it.

340
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:25,580
Looks like you're up next,

341
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,060
then Ding, then me.

342
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:27,900
You two are last, right?

343
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:31,340
Are you nervous, Ding?

344
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:32,620
(Pep talk mode)
If you mess up, just do it again.

345
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:34,220
What else can you do?

346
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:35,940
That's just life.

347
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,140
Okay, I'm off.

348
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:37,580
(Ms. Wen arrives)

349
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:38,900
(He Jiahuan enters)

350
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,140
(Ding cramming his lines)

351
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,020
Why did you suddenly start dancing?

352
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:46,620
(Wiggling)

353
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:48,540
Aren't I going to teach you all a dance?

354
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:52,180
(Exclusive: An family heir
publicly declares war!)

355
00:08:53,090 --> 00:08:54,940
The Full Press Conference.

356
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,780
(An Glass Factory: WELCOME)

357
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:58,020
Who will ultimately take
the helm of the An family?

358
00:08:58,700 --> 00:08:59,740
Alright everyone.

359
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:00,540
Let's get ready,

360
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,660
so we can start shooting!

361
00:09:01,660 --> 00:09:02,260
Okay.

362
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:02,620
Sure.

363
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,580
(Ready)
Let's start.

364
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:06,140
Alright, let's wait over there

365
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:06,940
for now.

366
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:08,140
Okay.

367
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:09,820
Who are we waiting for?

368
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:11,060
Waiting for the wind.

369
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:12,180
(Only Mommy gets it)

370
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:12,540
Alright.

371
00:09:12,540 --> 00:09:13,900
First up, Mr. Ke.

372
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:15,500
Mr. Ke?

373
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:18,540
They even let him go first?

374
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:19,580
(Who's talking behind my back?)

375
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,380
Mr. Ke!

376
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:23,460
Who are you to call him Mr. Ke?

377
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:24,580
(Bold)

378
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,180
(Excuse me?)

379
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,460
(Mr. Ke enters)
Mr. Ke.

380
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:29,660
The way you talk

381
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:30,980
sounds more CEO than
your own brother-in-law.

382
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:32,300
No, I'm not.

383
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,780
(Brother-in-law, hear me out)

384
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:35,460
Who taught you that?

385
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:37,580
(Sweet-talking An Xiaoding)
Brother-in-law taught me well.

386
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:39,060
(A little embarrassed)

387
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,420
(Fully professional)
Looking great.

388
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:43,660
Give me some artist's vibe.

389
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:45,100
An artist's vibe.

390
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,140
Artistic...

391
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,700
Right, do your own thing.

392
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:51,740
Beautiful.

393
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:54,460
(Watching the show)

394
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,220
(An-Glass-Artist-Ke)

395
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:00,260
(Instantly breaks character)

396
00:10:00,620 --> 00:10:01,980
(New approach)
Let's try melancholy.

397
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:04,660
Melancholy.

398
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:05,420
(Let's see it)

399
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,060
(Blue mode: activated)
A melancholy feeling.

400
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:07,900
Melancholy engaged.

401
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,900
(In character instantly)

402
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:14,860
Cinematic face.

403
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:15,740
(How'd that change again?)

404
00:10:16,020 --> 00:10:16,980
Cinematic?

405
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,220
Alright.

406
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,220
(Switches mode instantly)

407
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,340
Like reading a novel!

408
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:23,860
A picture book!

409
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:29,100
(Realist school · cinematic)

410
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:30,740
Now, let me interview you.

411
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,780
The public has always been curious

412
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:34,540
about the An family inheritance.

413
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:35,020
Yes.

414
00:10:35,020 --> 00:10:35,820
So Mr. Ke, why

415
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:37,580
have you chosen not
to compete this time?

416
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:40,540
(Waiting for your answer)

417
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:42,340
I have always been

418
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:43,980
a person who seeks
nothing from this world.

419
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:46,340
I simply love glass.

420
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:47,260
(Pursuing art)
I don't care for the family fortune.

421
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:50,460
A true artist.

422
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:52,140
Yes, a true artist.

423
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:53,220
My aspirations

424
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,820
go beyond these shallow...

425
00:10:56,980 --> 00:10:57,980
these shallow...

426
00:10:57,980 --> 00:10:59,420
(these shallow)

427
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,220
Hypocritical.

428
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,300
So what are your aspirations?

429
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:05,380
My aspiration is

430
00:11:05,380 --> 00:11:06,980
to make even more beautiful glass.

431
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,780
(Still shallow)

432
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:11,460
You'd better be.

433
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,460
(Applause?)

434
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:17,220
Mr. Ke!

435
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:18,660
Great.

436
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:19,580
Thank you, Mr. Ke.

437
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,020
You can wait on the side.

438
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:22,140
Sure.

439
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:23,340
Alright, next.

440
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:23,940
Our second group,

441
00:11:23,940 --> 00:11:25,020
Mr. Ning

442
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:27,220
(Grand entrance)

443
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,020
and Ms. Wen.

444
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:31,420
Am I shooting with my brother?

445
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:33,740
And Mr. He.

446
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:35,980
Come on...

447
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:36,780
Come on, all three of you.

448
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:38,820
I thought it was my brother.

449
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:40,540
(Instantly in professional mode)

450
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:41,820
The young ones.

451
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:44,620
(Fully Jin-mersed)
Let the kids have their moment.

452
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,300
Very nice.

453
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,180
Can you give us

454
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:50,020
a heart sign?

455
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:51,540
A heart sign.

456
00:11:53,420 --> 00:11:55,620
(Love bodyguard)

457
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,460
Honestly,

458
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:59,020
when I look at Ning and Wen's faces,

459
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,460
I get upset.

460
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:01,020
Why?

461
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:02,740
(Still in character)
Reminds me of An's ex-wife.

462
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:06,580
Mr. Ning,

463
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:07,340
why is it that

464
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,740
you chose not to compete?

465
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:09,780
(Sharp eyes)

466
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:10,540
Reporter,

467
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:13,500
you are the first person
bold enough to ask me that.

468
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,540
And the last

469
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:15,580
who ever will.

470
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:17,180
(That's my brother)

471
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:17,980
So commanding.

472
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,940
I'll only say this once.

473
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:22,860
I

474
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:25,140
don't need to stand
on a giant's shoulders.

475
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:25,860
Because I

476
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:27,460
am the giant.

477
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,300
(Giant)

478
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:29,660
I think the An family fortune

479
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:32,060
is best left to my
sister and her husband.

480
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:34,180
That's the best outcome.

481
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:34,900
Well said.

482
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,060
(Speaks to my heart)

483
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:36,660
What?

484
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,980
(Furious)

485
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:39,340
What's wrong?

486
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,460
He's completely ignoring me.

487
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:44,460
And you are?

488
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:45,580
Who are you?

489
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,220
I'm your mother.

490
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:50,420
I'm your stepmother.

491
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:51,060
Fine, Stepmom.

492
00:12:51,060 --> 00:12:51,740
(Letting it slide)

493
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:53,660
(Not listening)

494
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:54,580
So, Ms. Wen,

495
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:56,540
with two handsome men

496
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:57,740
standing beside you,

497
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:59,860
if your brother and your
husband both fell into the water,

498
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:00,620
who would you save first?

499
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:02,540
My husband would save my brother.

500
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:05,860
If my husband and my brother

501
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:06,740
both fall in the water,

502
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:07,460
they will stand up

503
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:09,340
and realize the water
only reaches their shins.

504
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:11,100
(Long legs save lives)

505
00:13:11,180 --> 00:13:12,260
(Smooth answer)
Fell into a puddle.

506
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:13,100
Exactly.

507
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,100
Good.

508
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:15,620
Now, Ms. Wen

509
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:17,740
and Mr. He,

510
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:18,340
I hear you two

511
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,940
have a very powerful campaign slogan.

512
00:13:21,060 --> 00:13:21,940
Campaign slogan?

513
00:13:21,940 --> 00:13:22,740
(You know it right?)
What is it?

514
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,580
(I don't)
What is it?

515
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:29,700
Between us two,

516
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:31,180
there will definitely be one

517
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:33,140
giant of the An family.

518
00:13:33,460 --> 00:13:34,860
(That's literally my line)

519
00:13:34,860 --> 00:13:35,500
Right.

520
00:13:35,620 --> 00:13:36,700
Is that even a slogan?

521
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:37,820
That's just a sentence.

522
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:38,900
Just a normal sentence.

523
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,540
(Sharp)

524
00:13:40,580 --> 00:13:42,340
(Not taking any rebuttals)

525
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:43,180
Okay then, same.

526
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:43,660
Let's wait

527
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:44,620
on the side.

528
00:13:45,140 --> 00:13:46,180
Thanks.

529
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:48,140
(Commanding entrance)
Let's go.

530
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:48,820
Mommy.

531
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:50,540
You stand in the middle.

532
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:52,580
Stepmom, showing us those
skin-tone leggings, huh?

533
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:53,500
(Little tease)

534
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:54,980
Can you fix my ankle area?

535
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,860
(Very warmth-conscious)
Because I'm wearing two pairs of socks.

536
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:57,660
You could never buy

537
00:13:57,660 --> 00:13:59,260
(The Truth S3, Tui City Mansion EP3)
any natural-looking skin-tone leggings.

538
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:00,380
(Already un-recommending it)
Girls,

539
00:14:00,380 --> 00:14:00,940
just give up.

540
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,500
Ma'am, look at that confidence.

541
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,580
You're clearly set on
securing the chairman.

542
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:06,860
(Already mine)
Of course.

543
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:08,660
That's all mine.

544
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:09,500
What about Mr. Ding?

545
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:11,980
My mom's right.

546
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:13,740
It's like comparing

547
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:16,820
top-grade cashmere against a garbage bag

548
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:17,780
in terms of value.

549
00:14:18,540 --> 00:14:19,300
Right?

550
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,620
(Cashmere)
PS: cashmere.

551
00:14:21,540 --> 00:14:22,900
Garbage bag.

552
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:23,340
Understood.

553
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:24,100
(Garbage bag)

554
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:24,900
But right now,

555
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:25,980
these two sides are already

556
00:14:26,580 --> 00:14:27,100
going head-to-head.

557
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:29,260
(All-out rivalry)

558
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:31,460
Three, two, one.

559
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:34,380
Let's do a classic
stereotypical villain face, shall we?

560
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:34,780
(Inspired)

561
00:14:35,220 --> 00:14:36,180
He's elegant.

562
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:36,580
Why?

563
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:37,460
(Born to perform)

564
00:14:37,460 --> 00:14:38,100
He's elegant?

565
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:38,980
He's always been

566
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:40,300
