(Fully understands the rules)
Yeah.

842
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:52,300
If you don't have points

843
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:52,860
and want to eat,

844
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:53,540
just tell me

845
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:54,900
that you're hungry,

846
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,300
and I'll treat you to a meal.

847
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:58,580
(Oh no. I don't have a meal card)

848
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,580
It's fine. I have a "dad".

849
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,420
He has zero points too.

850
00:23:02,940 --> 00:23:04,020
(Stay tuned for "Push Supply Station")
Now only Ding and I have points.

851
00:23:04,660 --> 00:23:05,900
(Waiting to be fed)

852
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:06,660
Morning.

853
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:07,580
(Zero-points Dad is here)

854
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:08,660
How did you sleep?

855
00:23:08,980 --> 00:23:09,820
(Not ideal)

856
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:10,340
Not great.

857
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:12,900
I keep dreaming for no reason.

858
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:14,060
Nightmares?

859
00:23:14,660 --> 00:23:15,100
Really?

860
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:16,060
Yes.

861
00:23:16,060 --> 00:23:17,940
You're the murderer.
You must be feeling guilty.

862
00:23:17,940 --> 00:23:18,860
I'm the detective.

863
00:23:18,860 --> 00:23:19,940
Not the murderer.

864
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:20,900
(Heartbroken)

865
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:21,860
Everyone's here.

866
00:23:21,980 --> 00:23:23,460
(The king of meal cards arrives)

867
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:24,620
See?

868
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:26,020
That's why we're father and son.

869
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:27,820
Of course.

870
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:29,540
No. I meant we both have glasses on.

871
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:31,620
I think only the three of us

872
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:32,700
look like we're in night robes.

873
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:36,420
(Pajama party)

874
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:37,540
Mine too.

875
00:23:37,540 --> 00:23:38,540
Yours is a night robe too.

876
00:23:39,060 --> 00:23:40,220
But theirs.

877
00:23:40,220 --> 00:23:41,380
Do you wear that to sleep?

878
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:42,740
Doesn't mine look like one?

879
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:43,940
Mine's a nightgown.

880
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,940
(Let me see)

881
00:23:46,020 --> 00:23:47,580
Doesn't the pearl dig into you
when you sleep?

882
00:23:47,580 --> 00:23:48,300
(Genuinely curious)
I like it.

883
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:50,060
(Doesn't understand, but respects it)

884
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:50,980
I just calculated.

885
00:23:50,980 --> 00:23:52,300
I think only the two of us have points.

886
00:23:53,020 --> 00:23:53,980
Why though?

887
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:54,820
Really?

888
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:56,060
What I meant is

889
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:58,820
only we get to eat.

890
00:23:58,820 --> 00:23:59,820
They have to beg us.

891
00:23:59,820 --> 00:24:01,780
(Holding all the power)

892
00:24:01,820 --> 00:24:03,620
(Bro won't let me starve)

893
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,420
So only you guys can eat?

894
00:24:05,420 --> 00:24:06,980
(Jealous)

895
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:10,700
You're too skinny.

896
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:12,140
I gained weight.

897
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:14,260
So thin.

898
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:15,740
(Stepping back for a better look)

899
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,820
I was skinniest around New Year's.

900
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:20,300
You mean going from 2025 to 2026?

901
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:23,460
Zhou Keyu, do you think you're fat?

902
00:24:24,340 --> 00:24:25,860
You two are basically the same.

903
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:26,420
But he still

904
00:24:26,420 --> 00:24:27,260
called you skinny.

905
00:24:27,260 --> 00:24:29,300
(Secretly pleased)

906
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:30,020
Where is Ning?

907
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:30,580
Oh.

908
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:31,260
(I'm here)

909
00:24:31,980 --> 00:24:33,220
What's this here/

910
00:24:33,220 --> 00:24:33,700
(Healthy tea)

911
00:24:34,020 --> 00:24:35,620
How do you say healthy in English?

912
00:24:37,620 --> 00:24:38,260
Healthy.

913
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:39,620
Healthy?

914
00:24:39,620 --> 00:24:40,420
That's it?

915
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:42,380
My English is self-taught.

916
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:44,220
I mostly speak really colloquial stuff.

917
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:45,740
The things you told me

918
00:24:45,740 --> 00:24:47,300
this morning are mostly

919
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:48,220
technical terms.

920
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:50,620
Psychology,

921
00:24:50,620 --> 00:24:51,060
right?

922
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,460
Psychology.

923
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:53,660
What, are you going academic now?

924
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:55,660
(Surprise)

925
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:57,460
You know English?

926
00:24:59,660 --> 00:25:00,780
Can you communicate

927
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:02,460
without problems?

928
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,340
Yeah, basically.

929
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:04,860
I'm jealous.

930
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:05,820
(A skill everyone envies)

931
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:07,220
Very fluent.

932
00:25:07,220 --> 00:25:09,220
He's my second English teacher.

933
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:13,060
(The unforgettable pun returns)

934
00:25:13,060 --> 00:25:14,180
Look more panicked, you guys.

935
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:16,260
Don't we look panicked enough?

936
00:25:16,260 --> 00:25:17,660
(Director Ning is here)
Let's act a little more panicked.

937
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:20,060
Don't make it look like we're
at the amusement park.

938
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:20,620
Okay.

939
00:25:20,700 --> 00:25:22,300
(Joins in instantly)

940
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:24,140
They really got a crane.

941
00:25:24,140 --> 00:25:24,580
It really is.

942
00:25:24,580 --> 00:25:24,980
Yeah.

943
00:25:25,780 --> 00:25:26,620
200 tons.

944
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:27,460
(The lucky survivor)
I survived.

945
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,380
Should I look outside,
so I don't feel so dizzy?

946
00:25:29,380 --> 00:25:29,980
No.

947
00:25:29,980 --> 00:25:31,060
(Sharing her experience)
Don't look.

948
00:25:31,140 --> 00:25:33,260
(Curious about outside)
Just spread out your focus.

949
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:34,660
(Wen never moves)
Don't just stare at it.

950
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:36,660
Actually, we can see

951
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,740
the layout of the set.

952
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:39,860
You're right.

953
00:25:39,860 --> 00:25:40,660
We already saw

954
00:25:40,660 --> 00:25:41,700
another set.

955
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:43,100
(Observing carefully)
The rooftop warehouse.

956
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:43,860
Rooftop warehouse's there.

957
00:25:46,340 --> 00:25:48,180
(Ning, the announcer, reporting live)
We've arrived at the warehouse.

958
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:49,380
We'll get on the helicopter.

959
00:25:49,380 --> 00:25:49,940
Seriously?

960
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:50,740
There's a helipad outside.

961
00:25:54,060 --> 00:25:54,940
Where's the helicopter?

962
00:25:54,940 --> 00:25:55,780
The helipad's next to it.

963
00:25:55,780 --> 00:25:56,220
(He is sharp-eyed)

964
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,340
It's just a helipad.

965
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:58,940
(Won't believe it)
That doesn't mean there's a helicopter.

966
00:25:58,940 --> 00:25:59,740
Helipad?

967
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:01,780
(Where is it exactly?)

968
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:02,340
No.

969
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:03,700
That's not a helipad.

970
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:04,460
You're overthinking it.

971
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:06,020
That's the show's logo.

972
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:07,260
The spinning thing.

973
00:26:07,260 --> 00:26:08,260
(So that's what it was)

974
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:09,100
(Suddenly reminiscing)
Do you know

975
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:10,060
what is one chicken and one chicken?

976
00:26:10,060 --> 00:26:11,540
Do you know what is one chicken

977
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:12,060
and one chicken?

978
00:26:13,620 --> 00:26:14,460
One chicken and one chicken.

979
00:26:14,460 --> 00:26:15,100
What's next?

980
00:26:16,020 --> 00:26:17,380
Yeah. What's next?

981
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:18,020
A punchline.

982
00:26:18,020 --> 00:26:19,540
(Confused +1)
One chicken and one chicken.

983
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:20,060
What?

984
00:26:20,060 --> 00:26:20,500
(Confused +2)

985
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:21,060
What is it?

986
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:22,260
I forgot.

987
00:26:22,260 --> 00:26:22,860
I totally forgot.

988
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:23,460
Me too.

989
00:26:23,660 --> 00:26:24,460
(Dead memories resurfacing)
Like button.

990
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:25,540
Smash the like button.

991
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:27,900
Fam, smash the like button.

992
00:26:27,900 --> 00:26:28,780
That's so old.

993
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:29,620
(Definitely an old meme)

994
00:26:29,820 --> 00:26:31,100
I'll explain it when we get back.

995
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:31,620
(Wen has more jokes)

996
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:33,460
Memorizing memes at home every day.

997
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:34,780
(Meme king)

998
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:37,140
There's another magical one.

999
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:40,340
What does a god ride?

1000
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:41,940
A god's ride?

1001
00:26:41,940 --> 00:26:43,260
(Thinking)

1002
00:26:43,420 --> 00:26:45,340
(Enjoying the show)

1003
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:48,820
Baby.

1004
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:50,260
Pokemon?

1005
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:53,140
Might as well say digital camera too.

1006
00:26:54,180 --> 00:26:54,940
This door isn't open.

1007
00:26:55,460 --> 00:26:56,220
Door's locked.

1008
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:01,460
So cool!

1009
00:27:01,460 --> 00:27:01,820
Handsome.

1010
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:02,540
Great job!

1011
00:27:02,540 --> 00:27:02,900
Careful.

1012
00:27:02,900 --> 00:27:03,660
Move inward.

1013
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:06,820
(Worried)
Careful.

1014
00:27:07,580 --> 00:27:08,340
Hang in there.

1015
00:27:08,580 --> 00:27:11,500
(The An family's only hope)

1016
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:17,660
There's a lock.

1017
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,300
You guys are locked in.

1018
00:27:24,460 --> 00:27:25,020
What do we do?

1019
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:26,420
We're not all
climbing out like this, right?

1020
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:36,700
Push one more person up.

1021
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:37,300
I think

1022
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:37,740
why don't

1023
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:38,300
we two

1024
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:39,460
send Ning up first?

1025
00:27:39,460 --> 00:27:39,900
No problem.

1026
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,180
Ning, help pull the girls from above.

1027
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:41,620
Is that okay?

1028
00:27:41,780 --> 00:27:42,460
Sure.

1029
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:45,300
I'll come back to help.

1030
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:47,980
Okay.

1031
00:27:48,620 --> 00:27:49,100
ALright.

1032
00:27:49,700 --> 00:27:51,380
It's easier this way.

1033
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:53,300
Three, two, one.

1034
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:53,580
Lift.

1035
00:27:53,580 --> 00:27:53,900
Go.

1036
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:55,060
Careful.

1037
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:02,340
That's a seriously long stretch.

1038
00:28:02,340 --> 00:28:03,140
Okay.

1039
00:28:05,180 --> 00:28:05,500
Okay.

1040
00:28:05,980 --> 00:28:06,380
Okay.

1041
00:28:08,660 --> 00:28:09,060
That works.

1042
00:28:09,380 --> 00:28:09,820
Yeah.

1043
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:10,860
Wait a sec.

1044
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:12,180
I'll go find some boxes
for you to step on.

1045
00:28:12,820 --> 00:28:13,580
Use the boxes as support.

1046
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:14,820
That works.

1047
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:16,100
Right, we can just stack boxes.

1048
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:16,580
Exactly.

1049
00:28:17,260 --> 00:28:18,260
Can we step on these boxes?

1050
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:18,660
Yeah.

1051
00:28:18,860 --> 00:28:19,300
Pass them up.

1052
00:28:22,860 --> 00:28:23,460
I'll catch them.

1053
00:28:23,460 --> 00:28:23,980
No problem.

1054
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:24,660
Okay.

1055
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:25,500
Yep, just like that.

1056
00:28:25,740 --> 00:28:26,260
Alright.

1057
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:27,500
(This area is dangerous.)
Move aside.

1058
00:28:28,820 --> 00:28:29,220
Coming through.

1059
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:29,700
Good stuff.

1060
00:28:31,340 --> 00:28:32,940
Careful not to cut your hands.

1061
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:33,580
Okay.

1062
00:28:33,580 --> 00:28:33,980
Got it!

1063
00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:34,460
Hold it steady.

1064
00:28:35,020 --> 00:28:35,300
That's enough.

1065
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:36,140
This is enough already.

1066
00:28:36,660 --> 00:28:37,420
Need more?

1067
00:28:43,900 --> 00:28:44,900
I'll help support it.

1068
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:46,140
Do I need to step here?

1069
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:46,780
Okay.

1070
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:47,900
I'm gonna jump, alright?

1071
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:49,580
Ready. 3, 2, 1.

1072
00:28:49,580 --> 00:28:50,660
3, 2, 1!

1073
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:54,980
Nice.

1074
00:28:54,980 --> 00:28:56,140
(Insane arm strength.)

1075
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:57,460
Amazing!

1076
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:57,980
Okay.

1077
00:28:58,220 --> 00:28:59,660
Wait, I can grab more boxes too.

1078
00:28:59,660 --> 00:29:00,420
Okay.

1079
00:29:05,580 --> 00:29:06,980
I'll look for more.

1080
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:07,460
No rush.

1081
00:29:12,100 --> 00:29:12,900
Wait a second.

1082
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:31,420
(Boiler Room)

1083
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:32,300
It's done.

1084
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:41,660
Awesome!

1085
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,740
Ding, you're amazing!

1086
00:29:43,740 --> 00:29:45,580
Had to be you, Ding.

1087
00:29:45,820 --> 00:29:46,660
You literally...

1088
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:47,580
Pried the door open.

1089
00:29:47,580 --> 00:29:48,540
You found pliers?

1090
00:29:49,100 --> 00:29:50,060
He forced the lock open.

1091
00:29:50,340 --> 00:29:50,900
That's impressive.

1092
00:29:52,940 --> 00:29:54,420
(Current state
of the An family tea party:)

1093
00:29:54,420 --> 00:29:55,820
(more snacks than dignity.)

1094
00:29:56,100 --> 00:29:56,820
What's this?

1095
00:29:57,500 --> 00:29:58,260
Signal flare.

1096
00:29:58,260 --> 00:29:59,380
We're supposed to signal for help later?

1097
00:30:00,260 --> 00:30:00,980
If we call for rescue later,

1098
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,100
is a helicopter actually coming?

1099
00:30:02,780 --> 00:30:03,420
Seriously?

1100
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:03,980
(Let me see.)

1101
00:30:04,020 --> 00:30:05,220
(There's really a helicopter?!)

1102
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:05,740
This is for real?

1103
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:08,100
I feel like we're gonna fly out of here.

1104
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:08,900
Really?

1105
00:30:09,460 --> 00:30:10,100
What do you mean?

1106
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:10,420
Okay.

1107
00:30:10,420 --> 00:30:10,940
We're taking a helicopter.

1108
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:12,580
(Curious baby mode.)

1109
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:13,380
A helicopter.

1110
00:30:14,100 --> 00:30:15,250
(Perfect hand gestures. Only missing the helicopter.)
The helicopter's here!

1111
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:16,540
They're coming to rescue us.

1112
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:17,820
(Already excited.)

1113
00:30:17,820 --> 00:30:18,860
Really?

1114
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:19,220
Really.

1115
00:30:19,220 --> 00:30:19,740
Maybe.

1116
00:30:19,740 --> 00:30:20,580
We're actually riding a helicopter?

1117
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:22,580
I've never ridden one before.

1118
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:22,980
Seriously?

1119
00:30:22,980 --> 00:30:23,660
Have you?

1120
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:24,900
Focus on solving the case first.

1121
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:26,900
(Business first.)

1122
00:30:26,980 --> 00:30:27,940
There are so many gloves too.

1123
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:29,740
We probably need these.

1124
00:30:29,740 --> 00:30:31,180
Maybe we have to wear gloves
to pull this thing.

1125
00:30:31,180 --> 00:30:31,820
Right.

1126
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:33,020
Is the helicopter really picking us up?

1127
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:34,940
There's actually a helicopter?

1128
00:30:34,940 --> 00:30:36,820
Can a helicopter
even fit this many people?

1129
00:30:36,820 --> 00:30:37,740
Yeah.

1130
00:30:37,740 --> 00:30:38,740
Two people can hang outside.

1131
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:40,260
Nice.

1132
00:30:40,260 --> 00:30:41,140
Like those super cool action scenes.

1133
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,300
The ladder drops down

1134
00:30:42,300 --> 00:30:43,380
(Aerial stunt performer)
and we just hang there like this.

1135
00:30:43,380 --> 00:30:44,700
Then Ning hangs outside like this.

1136
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:46,900
So cool.

1137
00:30:48,940 --> 00:30:50,340
That's basically James Bond.

1138
00:30:51,100 --> 00:30:52,220
James Bond-Ning.

1139
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:54,420
(James Bond-Ning.)

1140
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:55,580
James Bond-Ning!

1141
00:30:56,980 --> 00:30:57,700
Butler.

1142
00:30:57,700 --> 00:30:59,940
How about arranging some food
for us first?

1143
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:00,900
I can't cook.

1144
00:31:01,900 --> 00:31:04,180
Tell Pai to make us something.

1145
00:31:04,620 --> 00:31:05,500
Where's Pai?

1146
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:07,100
(Seriously asking.)
Where's Pai?

1147
00:31:09,260 --> 00:31:10,900
Pai is exactly where she belongs.

1148
00:31:13,940 --> 00:31:15,900
Where Ding and He Jiahuan are.

1149
00:31:16,260 --> 00:31:18,260
(Where Ding-baby and He Jiahuan are
is where home is.)

1150
00:31:18,580 --> 00:31:19,900
It's raining outside.

1151
00:31:19,900 --> 00:31:21,220
We'll bring everyone some food.

1152
00:31:21,220 --> 00:31:22,180
Take a little break.

1153
00:31:22,180 --> 00:31:23,340
Delicious.

1154
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:24,460
Let's share some.

1155
00:31:24,460 --> 00:31:25,220
(Being polite.)
Seriously, let's share.

1156
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:25,860
No sharing.

1157
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:26,380
Seriously, let's share it.

1158
00:31:26,380 --> 00:31:27,140
Just hurry and eat.

1159
00:31:27,140 --> 00:31:27,740
Let's share.

1160
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:28,660
Bro, no need to be...

1161
00:31:28,660 --> 00:31:29,980
No need to be polite with me. Eat.

1162
00:31:30,100 --> 00:31:31,100
(Dominant CEO Ding)

1163
00:31:31,780 --> 00:31:33,460
Why are you pulling
the domineering CEO act on me now?

1164
00:31:33,460 --> 00:31:34,820
You're really acting like a CEO with me?

1165
00:31:34,820 --> 00:31:35,540
This is so good.

1166
00:31:37,060 --> 00:31:38,220
Give him one too.

1167
00:31:38,220 --> 00:31:39,340
I already asked him earlier. He said no.

1168
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:40,300
You asked already?

1169
00:31:40,300 --> 00:31:41,300
I'm not eating it.

1170
00:31:41,300 --> 00:31:41,860
You must eat it.

1171
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:44,620
You want water?

1172
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:46,100
Who's feeding you?

1173
00:31:47,220 --> 00:31:49,220
You definitely look like someone
from the Electro team.

1174
00:31:49,220 --> 00:31:50,660
I didn't do anything.

1175
00:31:50,660 --> 00:31:52,180
Today he's acting like a CEO.

1176
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:53,860
Alright, you mother and son
can stop pretending now.

1177
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:54,820
I seriously didn't do anything.

1178
00:31:54,820 --> 00:31:55,740
(Trying to prove innocence.)

1179
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:56,980
You did absolutely nothing?

1180
00:31:56,980 --> 00:31:57,900
I did absolutely nothing.

1181
00:31:58,140 --> 00:31:59,500
(I don't believe you at all.)

1182
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:00,660
(Completely absorbed in food.)

1183
00:32:00,660 --> 00:32:02,220
This really is delicious.

1184
00:32:02,220 --> 00:32:03,500
(Foodie Wen)
Black sesame flavor.

1185
00:32:03,500 --> 00:32:04,620
(Strong food-exploration spirit)
What even is this?

1186
00:32:04,620 --> 00:32:05,980
(Expert Wen activated)
Black sesame pork floss sponge cake.

1187
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:09,540
Where did you buy this?

1188
00:32:09,700 --> 00:32:10,700
(Just one more bite)

1189
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:11,540
(Taste Buds of Tai City)
Delicious.

1190
00:32:12,100 --> 00:32:13,660
I swear there was only one earlier.

1191
00:32:13,660 --> 00:32:15,100
Why is there another one now?

1192
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:15,900
Ning secretly put one back.

1193
00:32:16,700 --> 00:32:17,900
Last night I offered you one
and you refused.

1194
00:32:17,900 --> 00:32:18,700
Now suddenly you want it?

1195
00:32:18,700 --> 00:32:20,300
(Strong recommendation)
Try a bite.

1196
00:32:20,340 --> 00:32:20,900
Break off a piece.

1197
00:32:20,900 --> 00:32:21,620
I'm not trying it.

1198
00:32:21,620 --> 00:32:22,580
(Controlling nighttime calories)

1199
00:32:22,900 --> 00:32:25,060
(Do not disturb)

1200
00:32:25,060 --> 00:32:26,100
(To fall in love with it is Ke's destiny.)
This thing is incredible.

1201
00:32:26,100 --> 00:32:27,260
Right? It's so good.

1202
00:32:27,940 --> 00:32:28,740
Amazing.

1203
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:29,140
So delicious.

1204
00:32:29,140 --> 00:32:30,740
I hate this kind of food the most.

1205
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:31,940
And you think it's amazing?

1206
00:32:32,780 --> 00:32:33,580
Then you two aren't compatible.

1207
00:32:33,580 --> 00:32:35,460
We could never live together with him.

1208
00:32:35,860 --> 00:32:38,860
Our zodiac signs just don't match.

1209
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:40,220
(Claims not to like it,
yet keeps quietly eating.)

1210
00:32:40,660 --> 00:32:41,820
You two actually
have pretty compatible zodiac signs.

1211
00:32:41,820 --> 00:32:42,220
Really?

1212
00:32:42,900 --> 00:32:43,300
Yeah.

1213
00:32:43,300 --> 00:32:44,380
Capricorn, Capricorn, Taurus.

1214
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:45,220
Pisces.

1215
00:32:45,980 --> 00:32:46,260
Pisces.

1216
00:32:46,260 --> 00:32:47,380
You're a Gemini, right?

1217
00:32:47,380 --> 00:32:47,860
What about you?

1218
00:32:47,860 --> 00:32:48,300
Capricorn.

1219
00:32:49,820 --> 00:32:50,620
Yeah, we're all...

1220
00:32:50,620 --> 00:32:51,500
(The Earth-sign detective squad.)
We're all earth signs.

1221
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:52,540
A whole pile of dirt.

1222
00:32:53,340 --> 00:32:53,660
So earthy.

1223
00:32:53,660 --> 00:32:54,100
(Very "earthy")

1224
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:54,740
You're all earth signs.

1225
00:32:54,740 --> 00:32:55,180
All dirt.

1226
00:32:55,180 --> 00:32:55,740
(All "earth.")

1227
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:56,860
No wonder

1228
00:32:56,860 --> 00:32:58,500
your detective squad only has...

1229
00:33:01,300 --> 00:33:03,660
Only has straight people and no weirdos.

1230
00:33:04,220 --> 00:33:05,380
Our squad has no weirdos.

1231
00:33:05,380 --> 00:33:05,620
Exactly.

1232
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,820
As if this group
isn't weird enough already.

1233
00:33:07,820 --> 00:33:10,220
You all count as "straight", right?

1234
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:11,980
You're analyzing us
through sketch-comedy logic now?

1235
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:12,400
Mm-hmm.

1236
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:12,900
(Completely exposed)

1237
00:33:12,900 --> 00:33:14,340
Now I suddenly
want to study sketch comedy.

1238
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:14,780
Mm.

1239
00:33:14,780 --> 00:33:15,860
What does "straight people" even mean?

1240
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:17,180
What's a straight person? A weirdo?

1241
00:33:17,180 --> 00:33:18,300
(Tips: "straight person" and "weirdo" are common comedy duo archetypes.)
No point hiding it.

1242
00:33:18,300 --> 00:33:19,180
(The "straight person" represents the normal perspective and reacts to the weirdo's absurdity.)
Just say things directly.

1243
00:33:19,180 --> 00:33:20,260
(As the emotional outlet for the audience, the “weirdo” acts silly and absurd,)
that's how Amazing Night explains it.

1244
00:33:20,260 --> 00:33:20,980
(using exaggerated nonsense to create conflict and punchlines.)

1245
00:33:21,100 --> 00:33:22,060
You watch Amazing Night too?

1246
00:33:23,020 --> 00:33:23,700
Who's your favorite?

1247
00:33:24,260 --> 00:33:26,300
(Pretty easy to guess, huh?)

1248
00:33:27,260 --> 00:33:28,220
Smooth.

1249
00:33:28,660 --> 00:33:29,020
Very smooth.

1250
00:33:30,780 --> 00:33:31,980
(I'm very satisfied.)

1251
00:33:31,980 --> 00:33:33,660
A little bit of humor.

1252
00:33:35,300 --> 00:33:36,260
Bam bam. Two punches.

1253
00:33:36,260 --> 00:33:37,180
(All soldiers of comedy.)

1254
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:39,060
You're really not eating any?

1255
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:40,140
Want a sandwich?

1256
00:33:40,140 --> 00:33:40,860
(He showing concern.)

1257
00:33:40,860 --> 00:33:41,340
Butler.

1258
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:42,380
(Nobody leaves empty-handed.)
Eat one.

1259
00:33:43,100 --> 00:33:43,780
I'm good.

1260
00:33:43,780 --> 00:33:44,380
Seriously, I'm good.

1261
00:33:44,380 --> 00:33:45,220
(Thanks for the concern.)
I already ate earlier.

1262
00:33:45,220 --> 00:33:45,940
We specially hired

1263
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:47,100
a Michelin five-star chef

1264
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:48,780
(Fully energized and ready to perform)
to make these sandwiches for us.

1265
00:33:48,780 --> 00:33:50,300
These are all from that place, right?

1266
00:33:50,300 --> 00:33:51,700
(Immediately joins the bit)
Exclusive supply for our family.

1267
00:33:52,420 --> 00:33:53,220
What does that have to do with you?

1268
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:55,540
No, we're a wealthy family, brother.

1269
00:33:55,540 --> 00:33:57,140
(Don't forget your identity.)
We're rich.

1270
00:33:57,140 --> 00:33:58,500
Right, aren't we...

1271
00:33:58,500 --> 00:33:59,620
(Forcefully trying to save face.)
We don’t really share a bloodline anyway.

1272
00:33:59,620 --> 00:34:01,060
(Too immersed in the role)
We're a wealthy family.

1273
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:02,940
What?

1274
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:04,620
(Uncle, why are you like this?)
What's that got to do with our family?

1275
00:34:05,660 --> 00:34:07,100
You've played poor guys
for so long you got used to it.

1276
00:34:07,700 --> 00:34:08,820
Have you ever played
a rich person before?

1277
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:10,820
(Sincerely asking)

1278
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:12,940
Yes.

1279
00:34:12,940 --> 00:34:13,780
I have.

1280
00:34:13,780 --> 00:34:14,420
Really?

1281
00:34:15,660 --> 00:34:16,860
(What kind of joke is this?)
Yeah, I've played rich people before.

1282
00:34:16,860 --> 00:34:18,020
Show us your "rich guy" vibe.

1283
00:34:19,580 --> 00:34:21,380
(Random passerby exits.
Mr. Ke makes his entrance.)

1284
00:34:21,420 --> 00:34:22,460
(Breaks character in one second.)

1285
00:34:24,780 --> 00:34:25,500
(This is hilarious.)

1286
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:27,340
Rich people are like very West Coast.

1287
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,860
Give us a rich-person laugh.

1288
00:34:29,340 --> 00:34:30,740
(Life is hard.
Mr. Ke now performing for money.)

1289
00:34:31,450 --> 00:34:32,900
Honestly Ning feels more
like a rich guy.

1290
00:34:33,220 --> 00:34:34,500
(Me again?)

1291
00:34:34,530 --> 00:34:35,620
(Ordering dishes already.)
A rich person's laugh.

1292
00:34:39,340 --> 00:34:40,740
(Evil wizard mode activated.)

1293
00:34:42,060 --> 00:34:42,700
How scheming.

1294
00:34:49,300 --> 00:34:50,010
That one's actually accurate.

1295
00:34:50,660 --> 00:34:52,530
(Performance perfectly delivered.)
You can hear the calculation in it.

1296
00:34:52,530 --> 00:34:53,420
The moment you hear it, you know.

1297
00:34:58,220 --> 00:34:59,020
(Big wedding special)
Our dance king.

1298
00:34:59,020 --> 00:34:59,940
(Next Episode Preview)

1299
00:34:59,940 --> 00:35:00,580
(This side is fully prepared.)

1300
00:35:02,020 --> 00:35:02,740
(Ready to start anytime.)

1301
00:35:02,740 --> 00:35:03,420
(Fully hyped.)

1302
00:35:03,620 --> 00:35:04,420
Come on, little train.

1303
00:35:04,460 --> 00:35:05,140
(Fully immersed in the chaos.)

1304
00:35:05,380 --> 00:35:06,140
You guys are having way too much fun.

1305
00:35:07,620 --> 00:35:09,020
(Start dancing.)
Wedding march.

1306
00:35:10,220 --> 00:35:12,540
(Comes with built-in soundtrack.)

1307
00:35:12,580 --> 00:35:14,380
(The old-school artists insisting
on handmade effects.)

1308
00:35:16,460 --> 00:35:17,660
(Easy work, easy work.)
It's a small scene only.

1309
00:35:17,780 --> 00:35:18,660
(We're all family here.)
Say it already.

1310
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:19,540
(The accent has completely taken over.)
Just say it.

1311
00:35:19,540 --> 00:35:21,140
You can tell at a glance
I'm the boss, right?

1312
00:35:21,140 --> 00:35:22,420
(Everyone else are employees.)
They're all my staff.

1313
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:23,220
(Relaxed fit.)
I'm dressed like this

1314
00:35:23,220 --> 00:35:24,020
and you still want me
doing silhouette shots?

1315
00:35:24,020 --> 00:35:25,500
(I get you.)
Put your arm around the waist like this.

1316
00:35:25,500 --> 00:35:26,580
(I get you too.)
Trying to show off the waistline, right?

1317
00:35:26,580 --> 00:35:27,140
The waist is over here.

1318
00:35:27,180 --> 00:35:28,340
(From the neck down, nothing but legs.)

1319
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:29,140
(Behind-the-scenes
of the robotic-style poster shoot.)

1320
00:35:29,180 --> 00:35:30,020
(Fully in character.)

1321
00:35:30,020 --> 00:35:31,460
(Serious & Refined & Upright & Cold)

1322
00:35:31,580 --> 00:35:32,580
(Elementary school fight.)
I'm the one who gets to inhale first。

1323
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:34,980
(As expected,
Wen is still the composed one.)

1324
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:35,260
Let's go.

1325
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:36,420
(Tiny mouth, deadly poison.)
Get up or you'll never catch up.

1326
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:36,940
(Every word cuts deep.)

1327
00:35:37,020 --> 00:35:38,180
What were we aiming at again?

1328
00:35:38,180 --> 00:35:39,220
(Still savoring the moment.)
Shoot the pig butt!

1329
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:40,060
(Shoot the pig butt!)

1330
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:40,980
(The obedient younger brother.)
Can it recover itself?

1331
00:35:40,980 --> 00:35:41,820
(The sister with ideas.)
Just use it.

1332
00:35:41,820 --> 00:35:42,660
(The battle-ready big brother.)
Try it and see.

1333
00:35:42,660 --> 00:35:43,620
(The imposing uncle.)
Just let it regenerate.

1334
00:35:43,620 --> 00:35:44,620
(Time to play.)
Want to mess around with it a bit?

1335
00:35:44,620 --> 00:35:45,900
They're all
inside the control room right now.

1336
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:46,900
(What do we do?)

1337
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:47,620
(Never expected this.)

1338
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:50,820
(Anticipating)
Give me a world-shattering high note.

1339
00:35:50,860 --> 00:35:52,420
(The whole village's last hope.)

1340
00:35:52,460 --> 00:35:53,220
(I'm not ready yet!)

1341
00:35:56,500 --> 00:35:57,620
(High-note showdown.)

1342
00:35:57,620 --> 00:35:58,580
(Completely stunned.)

1343
00:35:58,580 --> 00:35:59,980
(Volume up.)

1344
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:02,220
(Adjusting method.)
♪Little bunny, be good♪

1345
00:36:02,220 --> 00:36:02,860
♪Open the door♪

1346
00:36:02,940 --> 00:36:04,220
(Open up!)

1347
00:36:04,420 --> 00:36:05,540
(Volume up.)
Open it for me.

1348
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:09,180
(Volume up.)
Open.

1349
00:36:09,180 --> 00:36:36,900
(The Truth Season 4 Viewing Calendar)

1350
00:36:53,650 --> 00:36:57,650
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

1351
00:36:57,650 --> 00:37:02,090
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

1352
00:37:04,110 --> 00:37:08,270
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

1353
00:37:08,270 --> 00:37:12,490
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

1354
00:37:12,490 --> 00:37:16,260
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

1355
00:37:16,260 --> 00:37:20,370
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

1356
00:37:20,550 --> 00:37:24,670
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

1357
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:28,780
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

1358
00:37:28,780 --> 00:37:32,420
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

1359
00:37:32,420 --> 00:37:34,550
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

1360
00:37:34,550 --> 00:37:38,500
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

1361
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:42,660
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

1362
00:37:42,870 --> 00:37:47,020
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

1363
00:37:47,020 --> 00:37:50,580
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

1364
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:55,490
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
